y choose from 200 programs — many nationally and internationally recognized — to pursue their goals of becoming teachers, artists, engineers and everything in between. At UNT, students and their success are the utmost priority. Over 1,500 outstanding faculty call UNT home.  To ensure the success of UNT’s students and their contributions to society, numerous current initiatives are ongoing. Academic Integrity Curriculum Graduate Studies Toulouse Graduate School Internal Graduate Education Review Final Report UNT Final Report Graduate Student Recruitment & Retention Plan Innovative Enrollment Growth Initiative Mentoring at UNT Research Activities Summer School UNT Career Connect (QEP) This page contains pdf documents.  You can download a free pdf reader here. Visit Us   Office of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs370 Hurley Administration Building Mail Us   University of North TexasOffice of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs 1155 Union Circle #311190 Denton, Texas 76203-5017 [map]   Contact Us   940-565-2550 TTY: 940-369-8652 FAX: 940-565-2774 For questions about this website, contact ronda.bewley@unt.edu   Site last updated on: May 09, 2017 Disclaimer  |  AA/EOE/ADA  |  Privacy  |   Electronic Accessibility  |  State of Texas Online  |  Emergency Preparedness  |  THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information  |  UNT Compliance Hotline  |  Governors Committee on People with Disabilities  |  Texas Veterans Portal  |  UNT Home 